Package: clade
Title: Evolutionary Simulation of Behaviour, Cognition, and Sociality
Version: 0.5.18
Authors@R:
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "s.nakagawa@unsw.edu.au")
Description: Agent-based simulation of behavioural and cognitive
    evolution. Provides a modular framework for the three classes of
    interaction that shape behaviour, minds, and brains: between
    conspecifics (kin selection, sexual selection, cooperation, social
    learning), between species (predator-prey, mimicry, coevolving
    parasites, speciation), and with the physical environment (niche
    construction, phenotypic plasticity, seasonal dynamics, life history).
    Digital organisms carry heritable neural-network genomes (diploid or
    haploid) and one of six brain architectures (Bayesian neural network,
    multilayer perceptron, continuous-time RNN, gene regulatory network,
    transformer, or symbolic rule synthesis). Every biological scenario
    is cross-referenced to a primary-literature prediction and
    multi-seed audited against theory. The simulation kernel runs in
    Julia via 'JuliaConnectoR', with the R-to-Julia boundary crossed
    once per run. Parameter search includes MAP-Elites, CMA-ES (pure R,
    no external dependencies), and finite-difference gradient methods.
